N.Y. Comp. Codes R. & Regs. Tit. 22 ยง 218.6 - Remittitur

State Regulations

The remittitur of the Court of Appeals
containing the court's adjudication, together with the return papers filed with
the court, shall be sent to the clerk of the court to which the case is
remitted, there to be proceeded upon according to law. Any order to effect the
adjudication contained in the Court of Appeals' remittitur shall be sought, entered and enforced in the superior court. Notes
